1
00:00:01,768 --> 00:00:04,204
IT WAS DECEMBER 2, 2025

2
00:00:05,338 --> 00:00:07,741
A VERY SPECIAL MORNING

3
00:00:07,807 --> 00:00:10,944
FOR THE MEMBERS OF SCREWBALLS
WHO WORKED HARD THE WHOLE YEAR

4
00:00:11,511 --> 00:00:12,812
So,

5
00:00:12,879 --> 00:00:14,814
-it's the last shoot today.
-Yes.

6
00:00:14,881 --> 00:00:18,485
We prepared the real final segment
to be filmed on our way to Seoul.

7
00:00:18,551 --> 00:00:19,786
-On our way?
-Yes, there is

8
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:21,621
-a cafe on our way back.
-A cafe?

9
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:22,756
What's over there?

10
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:24,958
There will be a small event there.

11
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:28,128
As a token of appreciation
for all your hard work…

12
00:00:29,496 --> 00:00:30,997
GETTING BEATEN COUNTLESS TIMES

13
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:33,066
FLYING IN THE SKY TO DO MISSIONS

14
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:35,035
PLUNGING INTO WATER AS PUNISHMENT

15
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:37,137
CELEBRATING SO PATHETICALLY

16
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:38,471
DAZED

17
00:00:39,105 --> 00:00:40,640
ELSEWHERE

18
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:42,909
THEY ARE USED TO BEING TREATED DECENTLY

19
00:00:43,443 --> 00:00:44,277
Nice.

20
00:00:44,344 --> 00:00:45,545
DRIVEN SOLELY BY THE DESIRE
TO MAKE PEOPLE LAUGH

21
00:00:45,612 --> 00:00:47,580
THEY COMPLETELY DEVOTED THEMSELVES
FOR THE WHOLE YEAR

22
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:50,650
We prepared an event for you.

23
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:51,618
THE CREW PREPARED AN EVENT

24
00:00:51,684 --> 00:00:52,719
What is the event?

25
00:00:52,786 --> 00:00:55,388
-Could it be--
-Our parents aren't there, are they?

26
00:00:55,455 --> 00:00:57,724
Is it a final
celebratory performance for us?

27
00:00:57,791 --> 00:01:00,560
What could we be doing
at a cafe in Gapyeong?

28
00:01:00,627 --> 00:01:04,330
Come on. Why did you guys
prepare something so big?

29
00:01:04,397 --> 00:01:05,465
Do we have to dress up?

30
00:01:06,032 --> 00:01:07,067
I think we should.

31
00:01:07,133 --> 00:01:11,004
I think you can dress the way
you normally dress.

32
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:15,008
But the staff are the ones
who worked so hard. We did nothing.

33
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:16,609
-You didn't need to throw an event for us.
-Yeah.

34
00:01:16,676 --> 00:01:18,478
We should be throwing you an event.

35
00:01:18,545 --> 00:01:19,746
<i>Thank you so much for the food.</i>

36
00:01:19,813 --> 00:01:20,947
WE PROMISED THEM AN EVENT

37
00:01:21,014 --> 00:01:23,917
NO NEED TO GET SO TENSE, HEH

38
00:01:26,052 --> 00:01:27,987
Wow. This is really refreshing here.

39
00:01:28,054 --> 00:01:30,056
It looks totally different during the day.

40
00:01:30,123 --> 00:01:33,960
Everybody who came over
and slept at that house

41
00:01:34,027 --> 00:01:35,995
said that they felt
so refreshed afterward.

42
00:01:36,496 --> 00:01:39,199
The two-tiered beds you have.

43
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:40,100
Yeah, the bunk beds?

44
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:42,202
<i>-It was so cozy.</i>
<i>-Wasn't it?</i>

45
00:01:42,268 --> 00:01:44,737
<i>Yes, the mattress was nice in itself.</i>

46
00:01:44,804 --> 00:01:46,439
Wasn't the mattress so nice Sae-ho?

47
00:01:46,506 --> 00:01:48,041
I drifted off before I knew it.

48
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:49,109
You just drift off there.

49
00:01:49,175 --> 00:01:51,144
-I was so surprised.
-Upstairs was nice too.

50
00:01:51,211 --> 00:01:54,013
-Wasn't the upstairs nice too?
-It was so nice and cozy.

51
00:01:55,181 --> 00:01:57,317
What do you suppose
we'll be doing at the cafe?

52
00:01:57,383 --> 00:01:58,952
-I know.
-Games?

53
00:01:59,018 --> 00:01:59,853
ARE WE PLAYING GAMES THERE TOO?

54
00:01:59,919 --> 00:02:00,920
The final game.

55
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:02,655
You know what?

56
00:02:02,722 --> 00:02:04,557
We aren't just going to any random cafe.

57
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:06,426
Why are we going to a cafe

58
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:08,761
-that's 40 minutes out of our way?
-You're right.

59
00:02:08,828 --> 00:02:10,230
SOMETHING IS DEFINITELY UP

60
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:11,598
Which cafe are we going to?

61
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:16,169
What's this?

62
00:02:16,236 --> 00:02:17,303
We must have arrived.

63
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:20,740
IT SEEMS LIKE THEY ARRIVED
AT THEIR DESTINATION

64
00:02:21,407 --> 00:02:23,009
Darn it. What is that?

65
00:02:23,776 --> 00:02:24,611
What is it?

66
00:02:26,746 --> 00:02:27,981
Isn't that a bungee jumping site?

67
00:02:30,850 --> 00:02:32,685
-What's that?
-It's bungee jumping.

68
00:02:33,186 --> 00:02:35,288
The GPS seems to be taking us there.

69
00:02:35,355 --> 00:02:36,489
Isn't that a construction site?

70
00:02:36,556 --> 00:02:39,425
-Excuse me. I'll get out here.
-What is that?

71
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:41,427
I can't do that again.

72
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:43,163
-It's bungee jumping!
-Geez.

73
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:44,697
It looks different from bungee jumping.

74
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:47,133
<i>What is that? It looks different.</i>

75
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,268
SIMILAR BUT DIFFERENT FROM BUNGEE JUMPING

76
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:50,703
Wait. Why is it so high up?

77
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:51,738
We aren't going to a cafe.

78
00:02:51,804 --> 00:02:53,373
Being so high up…

79
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:55,375
-It looks different.
-It's called something-land.

80
00:02:56,075 --> 00:02:59,345
You know, look at how high up we are.

81
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:02,282
I bet it's going to be way scarier.

82
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:05,151
We probably won't all have to go on it.
Anyone but me. Stay calm.

83
00:03:05,218 --> 00:03:07,754
-What is this?
-In-seok, this is wrong.

84
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:09,322
I'm getting out of this car.

85
00:03:09,389 --> 00:03:10,990
WHAT WILL HAPPEN TO THE MEMBERS?

86
00:03:11,558 --> 00:03:13,726
Gosh, darn it. What is going on?

87
00:03:13,793 --> 00:03:14,627
THEY GET OUT NERVOUSLY

88
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:16,663
DISCOVERS THE PRODUCER

89
00:03:16,729 --> 00:03:17,697
Hey, man!

90
00:03:19,065 --> 00:03:20,400
What the heck is going on?

91
00:03:20,466 --> 00:03:22,569
Come on. This is just wrong.

92
00:03:23,303 --> 00:03:25,271
What is that? It looks different.

93
00:03:25,338 --> 00:03:27,006
This is wrong.
Where are you Producer Park?

94
00:03:29,909 --> 00:03:31,678
This is wrong, Producer Park.

95
00:03:31,911 --> 00:03:33,346
IN DENIAL

96
00:03:33,413 --> 00:03:35,215
Do you not want to see us again?

97
00:03:35,582 --> 00:03:37,150
THREATENING

98
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,885
-Is that bungee jumping?
-Hey.

99
00:03:38,952 --> 00:03:40,353
-Just tell us that.
-This is wrong.

100
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,754
It isn't all five of us, right?

101
00:03:41,821 --> 00:03:42,922
-The view is nice.
-Wait.

102
00:03:42,989 --> 00:03:45,358
-Are you wearing a collar? Let me grab it.
-Wait.

103
00:03:45,425 --> 00:03:46,893
-Are we bungee jumping?
-What is it?

104
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,361
-What are we doing?
-This is wrong.

105
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:49,429
-The view.
-This is wrong.

106
00:03:49,495 --> 00:03:51,164
Enough about the view.

107
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:52,432
That makes no sense.

108
00:03:52,498 --> 00:03:53,866
-Weather's nice too.
-What is it?

109
00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:55,368
We were having a good time.

110
00:03:55,435 --> 00:03:56,869
It says that it's 45 m tall.

111
00:03:56,936 --> 00:03:58,037
BIG SWING
TALLEST IN THE COUNTRY AT 45 M

112
00:03:58,104 --> 00:04:00,106
Man, that is seriously too high.

113
00:04:00,173 --> 00:04:02,875
Oh, my gosh. This is totally insane.

114
00:04:02,942 --> 00:04:04,477
Darn it.

115
00:04:05,044 --> 00:04:07,013
Please love and support the show.

116
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,448
Please show us a lot of support!

117
00:04:08,514 --> 00:04:10,016
<i>The start of our show's new season.</i>

118
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:11,184
<i>We survived, then.</i>

119
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:12,852
<i>We could return with a new season.</i>

120
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,554
<i>-Wow.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

121
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:15,855
AND SEASON 3

122
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:17,390
THE FINAL EPISODE OF SEASON 3

123
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:21,761
OUR MINDSET AS WE WRAP UP

124
00:04:21,828 --> 00:04:24,030
THE SEASON

125
00:04:28,701 --> 00:04:32,572
WE'RE SCREWBALLS AFTER ALL

126
00:04:33,406 --> 00:04:34,974
GLANCING OVER

127
00:04:35,041 --> 00:04:36,142
Listen,

128
00:04:36,209 --> 00:04:37,510
it can't be all five of us.

129
00:04:37,577 --> 00:04:38,845
Tell us what this is all about.

130
00:04:38,911 --> 00:04:40,847
Whatever, I just have to win.

131
00:04:40,913 --> 00:04:41,748
We just have to win.

132
00:04:41,814 --> 00:04:43,016
Sook, lighten up.

133
00:04:43,082 --> 00:04:44,984
You're on camera. Please lighten up.

134
00:04:45,051 --> 00:04:46,586
THE ENTERTAINER FORGOT SHE IS ON CAMERA

135
00:04:46,653 --> 00:04:47,887
You're on camera, Sook.

136
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,489
-Hear us out first.
-You're on camera.

137
00:04:49,555 --> 00:04:52,191
Let me get this settled
before we get started.

138
00:04:52,258 --> 00:04:55,895
I won't go easy on anyone,
not even if it's Sook.

139
00:04:56,596 --> 00:04:59,499
I already saw what we're doing.
I'm not going to go easy.

140
00:04:59,565 --> 00:05:00,733
What is that anyway?

141
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,736
That thing looks like bungee jumping,

142
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:04,904
but it isn't that.

143
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:07,273
Then, why is it
the "tallest in the country at 45 m"?

144
00:05:07,874 --> 00:05:10,376
Why does it have to be so high
if it isn't bungee jumping?

145
00:05:10,443 --> 00:05:11,978
Why did it even mention that?

146
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:13,913
I don't get it at all.

147
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:16,015
Please lighten up, Sook.

148
00:05:16,749 --> 00:05:17,917
Sook, you're on camera.

149
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:19,319
-There's a camera.
-You know,

150
00:05:19,385 --> 00:05:21,954
Sook provided accommodation
and fed all of us

151
00:05:22,021 --> 00:05:23,423
these past two days.

152
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:25,625
It would be the best
if she had to go on this too.

153
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:27,527
-What did you say, you jerk?
-The best.

154
00:05:27,593 --> 00:05:28,795
That would be the best.

155
00:05:28,861 --> 00:05:30,363
Let me explain.

156
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:32,231
This place is… Okay.

157
00:05:32,298 --> 00:05:33,866
There are stairs over there.

158
00:05:33,933 --> 00:05:37,170
<i>It's called Stairway to Heaven,</i>
<i>and you can take great photos there.</i>

159
00:05:37,236 --> 00:05:40,139
<i>And the 45-meter-tall thing</i>
<i>you saw over there?</i>

160
00:05:40,206 --> 00:05:41,674
<i>It isn't bungee jumping.</i>

161
00:05:41,741 --> 00:05:43,843
<i>It's an amusement ride called Big Swing.</i>

162
00:05:44,777 --> 00:05:46,779
<i>People call bungee jumping</i>
<i>an amusement ride too.</i>

163
00:05:47,413 --> 00:05:50,850
Don't you do bungee jumping
from about 45 meters too?

164
00:05:50,917 --> 00:05:51,851
The height is similar.

165
00:05:51,918 --> 00:05:52,952
So what's the difference?

166
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:53,986
Let me explain.

167
00:05:54,554 --> 00:05:55,788
You lie facing down.

168
00:05:55,855 --> 00:05:56,756
LAUGHS IN DISBELIEF

169
00:05:56,823 --> 00:05:58,157
Is it what we saw on TV?

170
00:05:58,224 --> 00:06:00,660
<i>-I pull it and let go?</i>
<i>-There's one in Seoul Land too.</i>

171
00:06:00,727 --> 00:06:03,963
I've done it, and that one
is scarier than bungee jumping.

172
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:05,131
Because I have to do it?

173
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:08,468
The scary part is going up
the 45 meters from below.

174
00:06:08,534 --> 00:06:09,602
<i>You're right. That's it.</i>

175
00:06:09,669 --> 00:06:10,903
You're right. That's it.

176
00:06:10,970 --> 00:06:11,804
SAYING IT SO UNAPOLOGETICALLY

177
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:12,739
SPEECHLESS

178
00:06:12,805 --> 00:06:17,343
It's an amusement ride called Big Swing
which is known to be a unique experience.

179
00:06:17,844 --> 00:06:20,413
It is the tallest in the country
at 45 meters.

180
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,415
-Did you drool?
-The same as a 15-story apartment.

181
00:06:22,915 --> 00:06:24,350
She practically spat.

182
00:06:24,417 --> 00:06:25,551
WHAT ARE YOU, AN ALPACA?

183
00:06:25,618 --> 00:06:28,020
-You feel the terror…
-My head hurts.

184
00:06:28,087 --> 00:06:29,956
…of the height of a 15-story apartment?

185
00:06:30,022 --> 00:06:32,325
Excuse us, viewers.
We're just so startled.

186
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:35,528
You see, they really didn't
inform us beforehand.

187
00:06:35,595 --> 00:06:37,096
-They just dragged us here.
-Jin-kyung.

188
00:06:37,163 --> 00:06:39,365
It really is just an amusement ride.

189
00:06:39,432 --> 00:06:40,700
What kind of ride is it?

190
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:42,935
Our staff came and checked it out.

191
00:06:43,002 --> 00:06:45,104
-Did they check it out or ride it?
-They rode it.

192
00:06:45,171 --> 00:06:46,572
-Who?
-The person who won the game.

193
00:06:46,639 --> 00:06:48,608
-Who… I see.
-They wanted to do it.

194
00:06:48,674 --> 00:06:50,743
-Then, go ahead.
-You guys go ahead.

195
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:53,212
Why do you want us to do it
if you guys are fighting over it?

196
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:54,781
How was it? Be honest.

197
00:06:54,847 --> 00:06:57,183
It's a bit scary the moment you pull it.

198
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,485
Do you go up on your own and pull it?

199
00:06:59,552 --> 00:07:01,320
You can go on your own

200
00:07:01,387 --> 00:07:03,022
or a few can get on it together.

201
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:04,023
-So this is--
-Darn it.

202
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,591
Just have one get on it.

203
00:07:05,658 --> 00:07:06,726
One out of the five of us.

204
00:07:07,493 --> 00:07:08,961
Couples do it too, right?

205
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:12,765
I'm sorry.

206
00:07:12,832 --> 00:07:15,435
EVEN SHOWING ABNORMAL SYMPTOMS

207
00:07:15,501 --> 00:07:16,369
Are you waking up?

208
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,337
I don't think I'll go on that today.

209
00:07:18,404 --> 00:07:19,472
I get that feeling.

210
00:07:19,539 --> 00:07:23,109
Regardless of getting on that or not,
I think I'm going to poop myself.

211
00:07:23,176 --> 00:07:24,544
This is driving me insane.

212
00:07:25,044 --> 00:07:26,045
Yesterday--

213
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:28,981
Everything I ate yesterday will come out.

214
00:07:29,048 --> 00:07:30,183
Geez.

215
00:07:30,249 --> 00:07:32,452
You see, when I was young,

216
00:07:32,518 --> 00:07:35,922
I went to Seoul Land.
That thing has a name.

217
00:07:35,988 --> 00:07:37,423
I forget what it's called.

218
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:39,325
-This is how you ride.
-It was on TV.

219
00:07:39,392 --> 00:07:40,226
Superman.

220
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:42,361
You go up lying like this.

221
00:07:42,428 --> 00:07:44,063
-Superman.
-You go up 45 m like this.

222
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:46,799
You have to pull something yourself

223
00:07:47,533 --> 00:07:48,601
at some point.

224
00:07:48,668 --> 00:07:49,802
Then, it just drops

225
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:52,038
as if you're gliding.

226
00:07:52,104 --> 00:07:53,105
I just imagined that.

227
00:07:53,172 --> 00:07:54,807
It goes like this.

228
00:07:54,874 --> 00:07:56,275
That's the tallest?

229
00:07:56,342 --> 00:07:58,945
<i>The view is so nice here,</i>

230
00:07:59,011 --> 00:08:01,914
<i>so I think it would look even better</i>
<i>from a height of 45 m.</i>

231
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:02,982
<i>Since it's the New Year</i>

232
00:08:03,049 --> 00:08:06,385
<i>and we're hoping that</i>
<i>all of you soar in the year 2026…</i>

233
00:08:06,452 --> 00:08:07,653
We're plunging. Come on.

234
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,088
It isn't soaring. It's plunging.

235
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:12,492
We organized this in the hopes
that you will soar.

236
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:15,127
Is there anyone who's dying to try it?

237
00:08:15,194 --> 00:08:18,498
We can give them priority.

238
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:20,233
Any volunteers?

239
00:08:20,299 --> 00:08:21,400
Gosh, you're so strong.

240
00:08:22,568 --> 00:08:24,971
THEY WANT TO SHARE THE LOVE

241
00:08:25,037 --> 00:08:27,974
Man, my stomach is rumbling.

242
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,376
Let me cut to the chase.

243
00:08:31,611 --> 00:08:32,879
I haven't seen that coin in ages.

244
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:36,349
Don't do that to us.

245
00:08:36,415 --> 00:08:37,450
How many have to do it?

246
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:41,454
Up to four people can get on Big Swing.

247
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:43,456
You get on it at the same time.

248
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:46,392
Sorry,
but I'll be leaving this show from today.

249
00:08:46,459 --> 00:08:47,727
I'm serious.

250
00:08:47,793 --> 00:08:50,396
I'm sorry I can't shoot
the final episode with you.

