my album this year.

501
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:06,992
They're opening the door
for the Big Swing.

502
00:17:07,059 --> 00:17:08,093
You can close it.

503
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:10,029
We won't be getting on that.

504
00:17:10,095 --> 00:17:11,930
-Sorry.
-You don't have to open it.

505
00:17:11,997 --> 00:17:13,332
We wanted to do it, but sorry.

506
00:17:13,399 --> 00:17:14,700
Gosh, that goes pretty high up.

507
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:15,934
I'm kind of scared.

508
00:17:16,802 --> 00:17:19,438
-Gosh, I'm getting a bit scared.
-You can do it, Sook.

509
00:17:19,505 --> 00:17:20,606
It's okay. You can do it.

510
00:17:22,274 --> 00:17:23,509
LET ME ENJOY THE VIEW

511
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:24,710
Isn't it scary?

512
00:17:24,777 --> 00:17:26,512
My legs are cramping. Gosh.

513
00:17:26,578 --> 00:17:28,580
If this is scary,
how was I supposed to get on that?

514
00:17:30,682 --> 00:17:33,619
CHANGING ABRUPTLY

515
00:17:33,685 --> 00:17:35,387
BUT A PHOTO IS A MUST

516
00:17:36,922 --> 00:17:39,058
Gosh, that thing is so tall!

517
00:17:40,192 --> 00:17:42,361
-Gosh, all five of us got heads.
-Sae-ho.

518
00:17:42,928 --> 00:17:44,596
It's 45 meters from there.

519
00:17:44,663 --> 00:17:46,465
-It isn't from here.
-Exactly.

520
00:17:46,532 --> 00:17:48,367
It'll swing outward.

521
00:17:48,434 --> 00:17:50,936
-We would fly all the way out.
-How far?

522
00:17:51,003 --> 00:17:53,939
You know, I bet In-seok and Eun-yeong

523
00:17:54,006 --> 00:17:57,443
-couldn't have even imagined…
-It wasn't in their plan.

524
00:17:57,509 --> 00:17:59,178
…this scenario at all.

525
00:17:59,244 --> 00:18:00,345
-Not at all, right?
-Exactly.

526
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:02,181
-I bet they're panicking.
-Am I right?

527
00:18:02,247 --> 00:18:03,816
This wasn't even in your plans, was it?

528
00:18:05,284 --> 00:18:06,919
I didn't even consider that possibility.

529
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:11,423
WHY DID THE 3.12% HAVE TO HAPPEN NOW…
SHOULD I BUY A LOTTERY TICKET?

530
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:13,826
You know what? Sorry about that.

531
00:18:13,892 --> 00:18:16,562
Sorry it just happened that way.

532
00:18:17,362 --> 00:18:19,398
One, two… Sae-ho.

533
00:18:20,299 --> 00:18:21,900
-Sae-ho.
-Aren't you taking a photo of me?

534
00:18:21,967 --> 00:18:23,735
One, two, three.

535
00:18:23,802 --> 00:18:25,003
TAKING A SELFIE

536
00:18:25,070 --> 00:18:26,505
-I thought it was for Woo-jae.
-Come on.

537
00:18:26,572 --> 00:18:27,573
DUPED

538
00:18:28,073 --> 00:18:30,109
HELLO, DRONE CAMERA!

539
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:32,277
One, two, three.

540
00:18:32,344 --> 00:18:33,645
THE DRONE CAMERA IS WASTING ITS TALENT

541
00:18:33,712 --> 00:18:34,913
One, two, three.

542
00:18:35,481 --> 00:18:36,315
Come down.

543
00:18:36,381 --> 00:18:37,883
THEY'RE ALL DONE TAKING PHOTOS

544
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,885
-Let's go. We can go home now, right?
-Yeah.

545
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:42,521
-Thank you.
-Let's go.

546
00:18:42,588 --> 00:18:44,389
-Good work, camera directors.
-How nice.

547
00:18:44,456 --> 00:18:47,226
-What a refreshing feeling this is.
-Thank you.

548
00:18:47,860 --> 00:18:48,861
In-seok is coming.

549
00:18:48,927 --> 00:18:50,796
HEY, OUR PRODUCER IS COMING

550
00:18:50,863 --> 00:18:52,030
Do you want to eat anything?

551
00:18:52,097 --> 00:18:53,465
-No.
-No?

552
00:18:53,532 --> 00:18:54,366
I'm too full.

553
00:18:54,433 --> 00:18:56,101
-Is there anything you want?
-No.

554
00:18:56,168 --> 00:18:58,237
This season's finale is just perfect.

555
00:18:58,303 --> 00:18:59,838
-This is what <i>Screwballs</i> should be.
-Yeah.

556
00:18:59,905 --> 00:19:01,406
Let me assign your seats.

557
00:19:01,473 --> 00:19:03,942
-No, we have to go. We have plans.
-Look.

558
00:19:04,009 --> 00:19:06,612
Lovely Mr. Goh, start the car.
Let's get going.

559
00:19:06,678 --> 00:19:08,814
I've never seen the staff so startled.

560
00:19:09,748 --> 00:19:11,550
I think our viewers will understand.

561
00:19:11,617 --> 00:19:15,087
No one would have imagined
that we could toss five heads in a row.

562
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:16,989
-Yeah.
-If we rode that, it'd be predictable.

563
00:19:17,055 --> 00:19:18,657
-So predictable.
-We'd just go, "Oh, no!"

564
00:19:18,724 --> 00:19:20,359
-<i>Screwballs</i> is never predictable.
-When we pull it,

565
00:19:20,425 --> 00:19:22,194
you'd film us in slow motion,
play some music,

566
00:19:22,261 --> 00:19:23,095
-and we'd fall.
-Yeah.

567
00:19:23,162 --> 00:19:24,663
-It's so predictable.
-Come on.

568
00:19:24,730 --> 00:19:25,831
That has been done for ages.

569
00:19:25,898 --> 00:19:27,065
-Exactly.
-So predictable.

570
00:19:27,132 --> 00:19:28,700
Do you know what's so shocking?

571
00:19:28,767 --> 00:19:30,402
At the last moment, Jin-kyung decided to

572
00:19:30,469 --> 00:19:31,637
-flip it.
-She flipped it.

573
00:19:31,703 --> 00:19:33,038
-She flipped it.
-I flipped it.

574
00:19:33,105 --> 00:19:36,175
-She flipped everything.
-I flipped all of our fates.

575
00:19:36,241 --> 00:19:38,310
-If I didn't do it, only I would survive.
-Right.

576
00:19:38,377 --> 00:19:40,012
I saved everyone by flipping it.

577
00:19:40,078 --> 00:19:41,213
You're right. Wow.

578
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,581
But this made me think.

579
00:19:42,648 --> 00:19:43,916
BUT THIS MADE ME THINK

580
00:19:43,982 --> 00:19:46,018
What if I got tails?

581
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:48,353
Stop. Do you want to
get on that by yourself?

582
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:50,088
It'd be four of us, not just me.

583
00:19:50,155 --> 00:19:51,490
-Stop it.
-That's enough, Woo-jae.

584
00:19:51,557 --> 00:19:52,391
Come on, Woo-jae.

585
00:19:52,457 --> 00:19:54,693
-I was just thinking.
-Come on.

586
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,161
Then, I'd think that too.

587
00:19:56,228 --> 00:19:58,330
What would have happened
if I didn't flip it?

588
00:19:58,397 --> 00:20:00,566
-Right.
-We understand how the staff feels,

589
00:20:00,632 --> 00:20:03,535
but you promised us. Let's be clear.

590
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:04,836
-No renegotiations?
-No.

591
00:20:04,903 --> 00:20:07,906
-He said, "No renegotiations."
-You said those exact words.

592
00:20:08,473 --> 00:20:11,877
Since all five of us got heads,
four staff members should ride it.

593
00:20:12,444 --> 00:20:13,345
What did you say?

594
00:20:14,413 --> 00:20:17,216
-We want to see how it works.
-Yeah.

595
00:20:17,282 --> 00:20:19,117
How about this? We'll film you.

596
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:22,588
We have nothing to do
so we can film you from below.

597
00:20:22,654 --> 00:20:23,655
-Okay.
-What?

598
00:20:24,489 --> 00:20:25,457
Then,

599
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:28,227
let me clench my teeth while I say this.

600
00:20:28,293 --> 00:20:29,628
We'll wrap things up now.

601
00:20:29,695 --> 00:20:31,096
You guys have to get on it.

602
00:20:31,163 --> 00:20:34,733
Are you going to stop filming now
and pick up where we left off next season?

603
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,768
YOU WANT TO COME BACK HERE?

604
00:20:36,835 --> 00:20:38,637
-Hey!
-No, you can't do that.

605
00:20:38,704 --> 00:20:40,606
-Why would you even suggest that?
-No.

606
00:20:40,672 --> 00:20:42,975
-You need to be kinder.
-Why would you

607
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:45,444
-even suggest that idea?
-You see,

608
00:20:45,510 --> 00:20:48,380
it was as if he was saying
we'll return when he clenched his teeth.

609
00:20:48,447 --> 00:20:50,382
-I'm not coming back.
-No, it's not that.

610
00:20:50,449 --> 00:20:53,218
I won't even pee in this direction.

611
00:20:53,285 --> 00:20:54,786
But you live in Gapyeong.

612
00:20:54,853 --> 00:20:56,355
I'm not going to Gapyeong anymore.

613
00:20:56,421 --> 00:20:58,123
-Don't do that.
-How about this?

614
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:01,493
-Forget about the staff.
-Okay.

615
00:21:02,127 --> 00:21:03,095
This is my suggestion.

616
00:21:03,161 --> 00:21:05,364
-Don't say it.
-You're just like them.

617
00:21:05,430 --> 00:21:06,832
-It's over so why bother?
-Go on.

618
00:21:06,898 --> 00:21:08,133
I trust Woo-jae. Go on.

619
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,368
-Just trust me.
-Okay.

620
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:11,436
-This is a suggestion just among us.
-Okay.

621
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:14,206
Should we just pick two people?

622
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:15,607
-No way, man.
-No.

623
00:21:15,674 --> 00:21:17,709
What the heck? Are you insane?

624
00:21:17,776 --> 00:21:19,044
What's wrong with you?

625
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:22,247
If it's only two people,
I'm certain that it won't be me.

626
00:21:22,314 --> 00:21:24,349
-Why do you live your life like this?
-No, thanks.

627
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:25,617
I won't do it. No way.

628
00:21:25,684 --> 00:21:28,253
-No way.
-Start the car. I'm on my way out.

629
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:30,822
<i>Let's wrap up already.</i>
<i>Let's say goodbye and wrap it up.</i>

630
00:21:30,889 --> 00:21:34,826
Thank you for your support
until the end of Season 3.

631
00:21:34,893 --> 00:21:36,228
<i>Screwballs </i>will

632
00:21:37,229 --> 00:21:38,363
not say hello

633
00:21:38,864 --> 00:21:40,565
to you from Gapyeong anymore.

634
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:41,700
WON'T BE RETURNING TO GAPYEONG

635
00:21:41,767 --> 00:21:44,736
And from our next shoot,

636
00:21:44,803 --> 00:21:47,406
when we receive notice
on where we'll be filming,

637
00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:49,541
-I'm going to look up all the rides there.
-Yeah.

638
00:21:49,608 --> 00:21:51,677
Happy New Year, everyone.

639
00:21:51,743 --> 00:21:52,611
Thank you.

640
00:21:52,678 --> 00:21:54,046
They should say something too.

641
00:21:54,112 --> 00:21:55,247
-Jin-kyung.
-By yourself?

642
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:58,350
I was so happy to be with our members

643
00:21:58,417 --> 00:22:00,452
and I think we proved once again

644
00:22:01,053 --> 00:22:02,387
-that we are one mind.
-Teamwork? Yeah.

645
00:22:02,454 --> 00:22:04,289
-And that we are one team.
-Yeah.

646
00:22:04,356 --> 00:22:05,924
When we return for the new season,

647
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:08,327
we'll make you laugh heartily

648
00:22:08,393 --> 00:22:10,329
the way only <i>Screwballs </i>knows how.

649
00:22:10,395 --> 00:22:12,898
Shall we act like we're flying
for the final cut?

650
00:22:12,964 --> 00:22:13,865
-On the floor.
-Okay.

651
00:22:13,932 --> 00:22:15,434
They can use the image at least.

652
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:16,902
-Happy New Year.
-Happy New Year.

653
00:22:18,570 --> 00:22:19,905
TAUNTING THE STAFF

654
00:22:19,971 --> 00:22:22,207
-Okay.
-Isn't it nice to say bye from the floor?

655
00:22:24,609 --> 00:22:25,811
Three, two, one.

656
00:22:26,611 --> 00:22:27,879
<i>One, two, three, four.</i>

657
00:22:27,946 --> 00:22:30,849
The rabbit that descended
from the sky said…

658
00:22:30,916 --> 00:22:33,919
-<i>Boom chicka boom</i>
-<i>Boom chicka boom</i>

659
00:22:33,985 --> 00:22:35,187
Bunny, bunny. Bunny, bunny.

660
00:22:35,253 --> 00:22:36,722
-Bunny, bunny.
-Carrot, carrot.

661
00:22:36,788 --> 00:22:37,622
ENTERING THE BUNNY CLUB

662
00:22:38,123 --> 00:22:39,825
-Bunny, bunny.
-Carrot, carrot.

663
00:22:39,891 --> 00:22:41,059
JUST ENJOY IT

664
00:22:41,126 --> 00:22:42,761
-Bunny, bunny.
-Carrot, carrot.

665
00:22:43,195 --> 00:22:44,129
FATAL

666
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:45,597
-Bunny, bunny.
-Carrot, carrot.

667
00:22:47,599 --> 00:22:48,800
FORGET ABOUT THE GAME

668
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,068
Woo-jae's gonna lose weight.

669
00:22:50,135 --> 00:22:51,803
THE BONEY BUNNY BURNS CALORIES

670
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:53,238
Carrot, carrot.

671
00:22:53,305 --> 00:22:54,773
-Bunny, bunny.
-Carrot, carrot.

672
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:56,208
Give me some carrot latte.

673
00:22:56,274 --> 00:22:57,709
A CARROT LATTE ON THE ROCKS, PLEASE

674
00:22:57,776 --> 00:22:59,778
THE BUNNY CLUB REACHES ITS CLIMAX

675
00:22:59,845 --> 00:23:01,446
Bunny, bunny. Bunny, bunny.

676
00:23:01,513 --> 00:23:02,514
Bunny, bunny.

677
00:23:03,014 --> 00:23:04,716
-Bunny, bunny.
-Okay. We got our ending.

678
00:23:04,783 --> 00:23:06,618
-I think this is it.
-Carrot, carrot.

679
00:23:06,685 --> 00:23:08,720
-Good work, everyone.
-Good work.

680
00:23:09,287 --> 00:23:10,422
Clap the slate, please.

681
00:23:10,489 --> 00:23:11,456
ABOUT TO DIE

682
00:23:12,023 --> 00:23:14,393
All right. Three, two, one.

683
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:16,895
<i>-Good work, everyone.</i>
<i>-Good work.</i>

684
00:23:16,962 --> 00:23:17,896
<i>That was hilarious.</i>

685
00:23:17,963 --> 00:23:18,797
GOOD WORK = "YOU'LL BE SORRY"

686
00:23:19,865 --> 00:23:21,466
THE ISSUE OF THE ENERGY

687
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:24,002
