993
00:33:43,955 --> 00:33:46,324
Do you like
Teto men or Egen men, Hye-lyun?

994
00:33:46,891 --> 00:33:48,326
To be honest,

995
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:50,061
I like Egen men.

996
00:33:50,128 --> 00:33:50,995
Why?

997
00:33:51,562 --> 00:33:52,930
Rather than men

998
00:33:52,997 --> 00:33:55,967
who are impatient and tough,

999
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:57,335
I prefer milder…

1000
00:33:57,402 --> 00:33:58,770
-And sensitive.
-Yes.

1001
00:33:58,836 --> 00:34:00,838
-I prefer that.
-What if he's too Egen?

1002
00:34:01,406 --> 00:34:03,341
He asks your opinion
on everything he does.

1003
00:34:03,408 --> 00:34:04,942
That's too much.

1004
00:34:05,009 --> 00:34:06,511
Didn't you initiate the first kiss?

1005
00:34:06,577 --> 00:34:07,445
Yes.

1006
00:34:08,479 --> 00:34:09,547
-Sae-ho.
-You're awesome.

1007
00:34:10,481 --> 00:34:11,716
-Yes.
-Do you still

1008
00:34:11,783 --> 00:34:13,885
ask your wife's permission?

1009
00:34:14,385 --> 00:34:17,488
Do you want a variety show answer
or a real answer?

1010
00:34:17,555 --> 00:34:18,389
-Variety.
-Real.

1011
00:34:18,456 --> 00:34:19,590
-Real.
-I want the variety show one.

1012
00:34:19,657 --> 00:34:21,192
The real answer is…

1013
00:34:21,259 --> 00:34:22,827
after I wake up in the morning

1014
00:34:22,894 --> 00:34:25,263
and get ready, I would casually

1015
00:34:25,329 --> 00:34:26,798
give her a kiss

1016
00:34:27,498 --> 00:34:28,866
without asking.

1017
00:34:28,933 --> 00:34:31,135
-Give us the variety show answer.
-The variety show?

1018
00:34:31,202 --> 00:34:32,403
The variety show answer

1019
00:34:32,470 --> 00:34:33,738
is that we don't sleep together.

1020
00:34:34,439 --> 00:34:36,207
I sleep in the pantry

1021
00:34:36,274 --> 00:34:40,578
and my wife sleeps in the bedroom,
so I'll text her to ask her if she's up.

1022
00:34:41,813 --> 00:34:43,147
"Excuse me. Are you up?"

1023
00:34:43,648 --> 00:34:46,150
But she locks the door,
so I say, "I'll pick it and get in."

1024
00:34:47,652 --> 00:34:49,087
That's my variety show response.

1025
00:34:49,153 --> 00:34:51,689
After I pick the lock to the door
and if she lets me in, I'll go in

1026
00:34:51,756 --> 00:34:54,792
and ask her, "If you are available,

1027
00:34:54,859 --> 00:34:56,727
may I kiss you?"

1028
00:34:56,794 --> 00:34:58,930
-You're very considerate.
-Yes.

1029
00:35:00,131 --> 00:35:01,933
The Very Easy Quiz show.

1030
00:35:01,999 --> 00:35:02,834
UNAIRED FOOTAGE FROM S3 E4

1031
00:35:02,900 --> 00:35:05,403
-Also known as Easy Quizzy.
-Easy Quizzy.

1032
00:35:05,470 --> 00:35:07,138
-Easy Quizzy.
-I like how it sounds.

1033
00:35:07,205 --> 00:35:09,574
Show us the next question.

1034
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:10,475
THE EASY QUIZZY SHOW CONTINUES

1035
00:35:10,541 --> 00:35:12,009
"Which areas need to be reduced

1036
00:35:12,076 --> 00:35:14,545
to cut production costs for <i>Screwballs</i>?"

1037
00:35:15,713 --> 00:35:17,682
Number one,
"The fee for the entertainers."

1038
00:35:17,748 --> 00:35:19,617
Number two, "The salary of the writers

1039
00:35:19,684 --> 00:35:22,086
who overwork their wrists
to find data and write scripts."

1040
00:35:22,153 --> 00:35:24,122
Number three, "The salary of the producer

1041
00:35:24,188 --> 00:35:27,125
whose bottom cramps from sitting
in front of the editing software."

1042
00:35:27,191 --> 00:35:29,760
Number four,
"The salary of the camera directors

1043
00:35:29,827 --> 00:35:32,296
who tirelessly film
every second of the members."

1044
00:35:32,363 --> 00:35:35,066
-There's no need to even think.
-There's absolutely no need.

1045
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:36,767
-What's the answer?
-Number one.

1046
00:35:37,602 --> 00:35:39,670
I think entertainers get paid too much.

1047
00:35:39,737 --> 00:35:41,139
JIN-KYUNG WILL RETURN HER FEE
TO REDUCE PRODUCTION COSTS

1048
00:35:41,205 --> 00:35:42,840
Especially, Woo-jae gets paid too much.

1049
00:35:44,342 --> 00:35:45,610
Woo-jae and Sae-ho.

1050
00:35:45,676 --> 00:35:46,911
That's a problem.

1051
00:35:47,478 --> 00:35:50,181
Then, if you would reduce your fee

1052
00:35:50,248 --> 00:35:52,383
who would you like to give it to?

1053
00:35:54,785 --> 00:35:57,889
FROZEN

1054
00:35:57,955 --> 00:36:00,725
Why would you ask me a question
that's not on the script?

1055
00:36:00,791 --> 00:36:02,927
If you could take a pay cut,

1056
00:36:02,994 --> 00:36:05,796
who would you give it to?
Number two, three, or four?

1057
00:36:07,532 --> 00:36:08,833
-I would…
-This is tough.

1058
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:11,068
EAGERLY AWAITING

1059
00:36:11,135 --> 00:36:12,170
No way.

1060
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:15,072
I choose number two. The writers.

1061
00:36:15,139 --> 00:36:16,207
THE WRITERS

1062
00:36:16,274 --> 00:36:17,375
Producer In-seok who sits

1063
00:36:17,441 --> 00:36:19,644
in front of the editing software
until his behind cramps

1064
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:22,013
must work just a little bit harder.

1065
00:36:22,079 --> 00:36:26,617
Even the camera directors who film
every single second of us…

1066
00:36:26,684 --> 00:36:27,919
THEY DON'T DESERVE TO BE PAID

1067
00:36:28,486 --> 00:36:29,687
THE CAMERAMAN SHEDS A TEAR

1068
00:36:29,754 --> 00:36:32,123
-How much harder should they work?
-Oh, geez.

1069
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:33,858
Our camera director is crying.

1070
00:36:33,925 --> 00:36:35,793
How much harder should he work?

1071
00:36:35,860 --> 00:36:37,495
-Camera Director.
-My goodness.

1072
00:36:37,562 --> 00:36:38,763
-How could she?
-Director.

1073
00:36:38,829 --> 00:36:40,431
-He's so sad.
-Do you like Guam?

1074
00:36:40,498 --> 00:36:41,832
Do you like Guam?

1075
00:36:41,899 --> 00:36:43,034
HE'S VERY UPSET

1076
00:36:43,100 --> 00:36:44,101
Let's go to Guam.

1077
00:36:44,168 --> 00:36:45,069
GUAM WON'T HEAL WOUNDS

1078
00:36:45,136 --> 00:36:46,470
I know you like dolphins.

1079
00:36:46,537 --> 00:36:47,405
Director.

1080
00:36:47,471 --> 00:36:49,574
You look like me, you know.

1081
00:36:50,241 --> 00:36:53,010
LET'S BE GOOD FRIENDS SINCE WE LOOK ALIKE

1082
00:36:53,578 --> 00:36:55,112
In your life, have you ever

1083
00:36:55,179 --> 00:36:58,716
had a moment
that you felt like the gods helped you?

1084
00:36:58,783 --> 00:37:00,918
-The gods helped me?
-Yes, a time that they helped you.

1085
00:37:00,985 --> 00:37:03,988
-If you have any, can you share it?
-This is what I remember.

1086
00:37:04,055 --> 00:37:05,923
<i>When we started out in our past lives,</i>

1087
00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:08,392
<i>when I was made the offer</i>

1088
00:37:08,459 --> 00:37:10,628
to join this team,

1089
00:37:11,128 --> 00:37:13,064
it was thrilling.

1090
00:37:14,498 --> 00:37:17,501
This was going to be
a very huge chance for me.

1091
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:19,570
That's the feeling I got.

1092
00:37:19,637 --> 00:37:21,906
-So you felt like the gods helped you…
-Helped me join.

1093
00:37:21,973 --> 00:37:23,741
-… join this show.
-Yes. That moment.

1094
00:37:24,709 --> 00:37:26,210
Let's all pick a favorite episode.

1095
00:37:26,711 --> 00:37:28,045
What's yours, Woo-young?

1096
00:37:28,112 --> 00:37:29,247
Mine would be

1097
00:37:29,947 --> 00:37:31,282
the first episode.

1098
00:37:31,349 --> 00:37:32,283
Killer Boot Camp?

1099
00:37:32,350 --> 00:37:33,851
-That day was…
-Yes.

1100
00:37:33,918 --> 00:37:34,919
Gosh.

1101
00:37:36,454 --> 00:37:37,989
HE GETS EMOTIONAL

1102
00:37:38,055 --> 00:37:39,857
-What's wrong?
-Did something get in your eye?

1103
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:41,459
Can you blow on it, Sae-ho?

1104
00:37:42,093 --> 00:37:43,194
<i>I should've cried earlier.</i>

1105
00:37:45,396 --> 00:37:46,397
The first episode was…

1106
00:37:47,231 --> 00:37:48,199
Gosh.

1107
00:37:48,766 --> 00:37:50,868
It felt very strange.

1108
00:37:50,935 --> 00:37:53,271
It felt like we were returning
from a previous shoot.

1109
00:37:53,337 --> 00:37:55,273
It felt very strange but very familiar.

1110
00:37:55,339 --> 00:37:58,209
Isn't that the scene
where Woo-jae comes walking out?

1111
00:37:58,276 --> 00:37:59,277
<i>He picks up the coin.</i>

1112
00:37:59,343 --> 00:38:01,579
<i>-Yeah.</i>
<i>-When he did that,</i>

1113
00:38:01,646 --> 00:38:04,448
<i>I had a mix of strange feelings surfacing.</i>

1114
00:38:08,552 --> 00:38:09,520
<i>A 500-won coin</i>

1115
00:38:10,254 --> 00:38:11,422
<i>showing heads?</i>

1116
00:38:15,159 --> 00:38:15,993
-Let's do it!
-Let's do it!

1117
00:38:16,060 --> 00:38:18,262
SCREWBALLS

1118
00:38:18,329 --> 00:38:21,699
FROM THE MOMENT
YOU AND I BEGAN

1119
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:26,170
EVERYTHING CHANGED
IT FEELS STRANGE

1120
00:38:26,237 --> 00:38:27,071
You failed!

1121
00:38:27,138 --> 00:38:28,439
I MUST BE TRAPPED

1122
00:38:28,506 --> 00:38:29,373
I love you.

1123
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:31,475
IN YOUR GAZE

1124
00:38:31,542 --> 00:38:35,212
TIME MUST HAVE STOPPED

1125
00:38:35,279 --> 00:38:37,148
WITHIN THE FLOW THAT CONNECTS YOU AND ME

1126
00:38:37,214 --> 00:38:40,351
I'M DRAWN TO YOU

1127
00:38:40,418 --> 00:38:42,953
I THINK I HAVE TO TAKE THIS TO THE END

1128
00:38:43,020 --> 00:38:44,355
What's going on?

1129
00:38:44,422 --> 00:38:47,224
I CAN'T STOP
WHEN I SEE YOU

1130
00:38:47,291 --> 00:38:53,564
MY HEART KEEPS
GETTING DRAWN TOWARDS YOU

1131
00:38:53,631 --> 00:38:55,266
<i>This is fun. He hit his head.</i>

1132
00:38:55,333 --> 00:38:57,835
MY HEART SWELLS
WITH EXCITEMENT

1133
00:38:57,902 --> 00:39:00,471
WE'RE JUST GETTING STARTED

1134
00:39:00,538 --> 00:39:02,740
AS LONG AS WE ARE TOGETHER

1135
00:39:02,807 --> 00:39:03,908
Look at my helmet!

1136
00:39:05,276 --> 00:39:09,280
NOTHING IN THIS WORLD
CAN STOP US

1137
00:39:09,347 --> 00:39:12,249
I BELIEVE IN THE LOVE
BETWEEN YOU AND ME

1138
00:39:12,316 --> 00:39:16,721
LET'S RUN TOGETHER
ALL THE WAY TO THE END

1139
00:39:16,787 --> 00:39:19,023
WE'LL NEVER STOP

1140
00:39:19,090 --> 00:39:22,293
WE'RE JUST GETTING STARTED

1141
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:26,030
WE ARE NOT AFRAID
BECAUSE WE'RE TOGETHER

1142
00:39:26,097 --> 00:39:29,867
IF YOU AND I HOLD HANDS

1143
00:39:29,934 --> 00:39:34,305
WE CAN WITHSTAND
ANY DIFFICULTY

1144
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:37,375
YOU'VE BECOME MY WORLD

1145
00:39:37,441 --> 00:39:39,043
AND I WILL PROTECT YOU

1146
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:42,313
I CAN'T STOP
WHEN I SEE YOU

1147
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:48,452
MY HEART KEEPS
GETTING DRAWN TOWARDS YOU

1148
00:39:48,519 --> 00:39:52,456
IS THIS WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO HAVE A FLUTTERING HEART

1149
00:39:52,523 --> 00:39:54,925
WE'RE JUST GETTING STARTED

1150
00:39:55,459 --> 00:39:57,061
My mom doesn't like you either!

1151
00:39:57,128 --> 00:39:59,730
AS LONG AS
WE ARE TOGETHER

1152
00:39:59,797 --> 00:40:02,767
NOTHING IN THIS WORLD
CAN STOP US

1153
00:40:02,833 --> 00:40:03,667
I lost.

1154
00:40:03,734 --> 00:40:06,737
I BELIEVE IN THE LOVE
BETWEEN YOU AND ME

1155
00:40:07,505 --> 00:40:10,674
<i>I was wondering if you could</i>
<i>act like you can hear the music.</i>

1156
00:40:11,842 --> 00:40:13,577
<i>That felt amazing!</i>

1157
00:40:13,644 --> 00:40:16,480
WE WON'T EVER STOP

1158
00:40:16,547 --> 00:40:18,215
"Thanks to you, I had a lot of fun."

1159
00:40:18,282 --> 00:40:20,651
I'LL PROTECT YOU UNTIL THE END

1160
00:40:20,718 --> 00:40:23,154
WE'RE JUST GETTING STARTED

1161
00:40:23,220 --> 00:40:24,855
I LOVE YOU

1162
00:40:24,922 --> 00:40:27,691
LET'S DO THIS TOGETHER

1163
00:40:35,900 --> 00:40:37,001
Let's turn.

1164
00:40:37,067 --> 00:40:38,335
We did it!

1165
00:40:48,679 --> 00:40:50,748
-Five!
-Five!

1166
00:40:58,923 --> 00:41:03,828
SCREWBALLS WILL RETURN FOR SEASON 4

1167
00:41:04,195 --> 00:41:06,197
Subtitle translation by: Ilyoung Kim
